==English==

===Pronunciation===
*:Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-æɡ|-æɡ]]

====Noun====
{{en-noun}}

# A small horse; an old female horse; a pony; hence, any horse.
# {{rfv-sense}} A [[paramour]]; -- in contempt.
# One who [[#Verb|nags]].

===Translations===

*[[Novial]]: [[kavalache]] ''m'' or ''f'', [[kavalacha]] ''f''

===Verb===
{{en-verb|nag|g|ing}}

# To bother with [[persistent]] memories.
#:''The notion that he forgot something '''nagged''' him the rest of the day.''
# To repeatedly [[complain]] about [[insignificant]] matters. 
